.TH "dwc2_hsotg_set_ep_maxpacket" 9 "dwc2_hsotg_set_ep_maxpacket" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dwc2_hsotg_set_ep_maxpacket \- set endpoint's max-packet field
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" dwc2_hsotg_set_ep_maxpacket
.BI "(struct dwc2_hsotg *hsotg "  ","
.BI "unsigned int ep "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mps "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mc "  ","
.BI "unsigned int dir_in "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hsotg" 12
The driver state.
.IP "ep" 12
The index number of the endpoint
.IP "mps" 12
The maximum packet size in bytes
.IP "mc" 12
The multicount value
.IP "dir_in" 12
True if direction is in.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Configure the maximum packet size for the given endpoint, updating
the hardware control registers to reflect this.
